The paper proposes a method for node embedding in temporal graphs, which involves learning the evolution of nodes and edges over time and incorporating this dynamics in a temporal node embedding framework for different graph prediction tasks. This work is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SD), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
